text: thumb|300px|right| The 2011 Staffordshire Moorlands District Council election is took place on 5 May 2011 to elect members of Staffordshire Moorlands District Council in England. This was on the same day as other local elections. After the election, the composition of the council was: *Conservative 26 *Independent 10 *Labour 7 *Moorlands Democratic Alliance 5 *Liberal Democrat 4 *Staffordshire Independent Group 3 *UKIP 1 ==Ward results== The candidates highlighted in bold were elected to each ward. ==References== * 2011 election results * 2007 election results Category:2011 English local elections 2011 Category:21st century in Staffordshire
title: 2011 Staffordshire Moorlands District Council election
